<language>
	<entry name="Academy0" value="Training Facility"/>
	<entry name="Academy0Description" value="The Training Facility provides our troops with thorough training in the ways of war and the use of all available technologies. <br/><br/><style oblique='1'/>&quot;The aim of military training is not just to prepare men for battle, but to make them long for it.&quot;<br/>    -- Louis Simpson"/>
	<entry name="Academy0Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+1 <icon texture='Attributes/Rank'/> rank for new units"/>
	<entry name="Academy1" value="Equipment Modification"/>
	<entry name="Academy1Description" value="War games allow the military force to pinpoint strengths and weaknesses among the troops. Measures can subsequently be taken, such as the reorganization of regiments and, perhaps more importantly, the modification of a good part of the vehicles and weapons to better compensate for the weaknesses, and rely upon the strengths, of their users."/>
	<entry name="Academy1Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+2 <icon texture='Attributes/Rank'/> rank for new units"/>
	<entry name="Academy2" value="Gordian Database"/>
	<entry name="Academy2Description" value="Mankind has a long history of war. Rather than accomodate the various hazards of battle by sheer improvization, the Gordian Database provides our troops with a direct neural link to a list of historical and recent conflicts, their known resolution as well as various calculations based on hypothetical moves, greatly tipping the scales in our favor."/>
	<entry name="Academy2Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+4 <icon texture='Attributes/Rank'/> rank for new units"/>
	<entry name="BlackHoleBuilding" value="Black Hole Generator"/>
	<entry name="BlackHoleBuildingDescription" value="This military application of particle accelerators produces collisions between particles with an energy of several zettaelectronvolts, focused on one single goal: the creation of macroscopical, volatile black holes. So far the results are overwhelming, though the time required to build sufficient energy is a massive drawback."/>
	<entry name="BlackHoleBuildingProperties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>Provides a Black Hole operation every 20 turns"/>
	<entry name="Credits0" value="Planetary Stock Market"/>
	<entry name="Credits0Description" value="Stock exchange provides an organized market for purchasing and selling of corporate and other securities per well-defined rules and regulations. This is indispensable for the smooth and orderly functioning of the corporate sector in a free market economy.<br/><br/>A stock exchange need not be treated as a place for speculation or a gambling den. It should act as a place for safe and profitable investment."/>
	<entry name="Credits0Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+12 <icon texture='Resources/Credits'/> credits"/>
	<entry name="Credits1" value="Market Regulator"/>
	<entry name="Credits1Description" value="The analysis of market structures affects trading costs and whether one structure is more efficient than another. It also allows the creation of establishments which oversee the market and enforce an optimal structure."/>
	<entry name="Credits1Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+50% <icon texture='Resources/Credits'/> credits"/>
	<entry name="Credits2" value="Credit Forge"/>
	<entry name="Credits2Description" value="The injection of credits into the market can help rectify minor problems, back and boost perennial projects, and save small-scale industry from bankruptcy. Once the colony starts making their own money, nothing can stand in the way of its development."/>
	<entry name="Credits2Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+100% <icon texture='Resources/Credits'/> credits"/>
	<entry name="Defense0" value="Adaptive Tactical Barricades"/>
	<entry name="Defense0Description" value="While constructing static fortifications to block passages and provide a military advantage is a priceless defensive boon, it has always suffered from the lack of instantaneous deployment and adaptability. Adaptive field fortification devices can be deployed immendiately after a threat is identified and will form a structure based on its field configuration and environment parameters. The dynamic nature of the structure allows it to be easily repacked after the threat has passed to provide free passage and keep the economic impact as low as possible."/>
	<entry name="Defense0Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+50% <icon texture='Attributes/Power'/> power for defending units"/>
	<entry name="Defense1" value="Defense Network"/>
	<entry name="Defense1Description" value="The Defense Network is a modular countermeasure system integrated within the very structure of the colony, able to counter any and all kinds of known menace with suitable means ranging from gravitational domes to coilguns and ICE. "/>
	<entry name="Defense1Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+100% <icon texture='Attributes/Power'/> power for defending units"/>
	<entry name="Defense2" value="Planetary Fortress"/>
	<entry name="Defense2Description" value="The Planetary Fortress is a sentient paramilitary superstructure dedicated to the analysis of potential and effective incoming threats. Its ability to grant almost immediate material support and assign idle troops where they are most needed is of the essence in any modern conflict."/>
	<entry name="Defense2Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+200% <icon texture='Attributes/Power'/> power for defending units"/>
	<entry name="EMPBeamBuilding" value="EMP Satellite Uplink"/>
	<entry name="EMPBeamBuildingDescription" value="Slowly building up energy from solar flares, the EMP satellite is able to transfer part of the ion storms towards the surface of Pandora in a high-powered, concentrated beam that disables defenses and cripples production of its target."/>
	<entry name="EMPBeamBuildingProperties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>Provides an EMP Beam operation every 10 turns"/>
	<entry name="Food0" value="Cultivation Facility"/>
	<entry name="Food0Description" value="Very similar to our old Earth, Pandora is host to a variety of ecoregions, ranging from the frozen ice lands at the poles to vast deserts and rain forests near the equator. With food supply being a primary concern for new colonies, this newly developed fertilizer allows plant growth even in the most desolate climates and on nutrient-poor soil."/>
	<entry name="Food0Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+4 <icon texture='Resources/Food'/> food"/>
	<entry name="Food1" value="Plant Air Suspension Relay"/>
	<entry name="Food1Description" value="Suspending plants in the air inside support structures allows for precise growth regulation. Oxygen and other nutrients come in contact directly with the plant's roots, fully bypassing the inefficiencies of an aggregate medium."/>
	<entry name="Food1Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+50% <icon texture='Resources/Food'/> food"/>
	<entry name="Food2" value="Food Replicator"/>
	<entry name="Food2Description" value="Growing plants seems inefficient at this point, since we have the technology to simply replicate food.<br/><br/>A replicator works by rearranging subatomic particles, which are abundant everywhere in the universe, to form molecules and arrange those molecules to form objects. Since matter patterns are stored at a molecular level it is only possible to replicate objects with simple quantum structures, such as food.<br/><br/><style oblique='1'/>Some people still refuse to eat replicated food, instead opting for the lengthy process of growing and preparing a meal like in the old times."/>
	<entry name="Food2Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+100% <icon texture='Resources/Food'/> food"/>
	<entry name="Minerals0" value="Refining Array"/>
	<entry name="Minerals0Description" value="Minerals no longer have to be discarded if they do not pass the minimum purity threshold, but can now instead be refined into a smaller mass of minerals that are satisfactory for production purposes."/>
	<entry name="Minerals0Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+4 <icon texture='Resources/Minerals'/> minerals"/>
	<entry name="Minerals1" value="Drone Excavation Center"/>
	<entry name="Minerals1Description" value="The drone excavation center allows each miner to supervise a number of drones at his mineral site. The use of these robotic programmed drones has proven to be invaluable thanks to their cuttinng-edge sensory and excavation lasers.<br/><br/><style oblique='1'/>There has only been one accident so far, where a drone undergoing maintenance detected the human supervisor as the mining target and shot a laser beam right through his chest. The drone continued operation following standard mining protocols, but no details have been released."/>
	<entry name="Minerals1Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+50% <icon texture='Resources/Minerals'/> minerals"/>
	<entry name="Minerals2" value="Mineral Warp Relay"/>
	<entry name="Minerals2Description" value="Advances in warping technology have enabled the construction and use of relays to perform so-called microwarps to extract minerals out of stationary mineral sources. These warps are so precise they are able to transport individual particles, but require substantial calculation and preparation in order to be successful. Even so, equipped with appropriate scanning equipment, we are able to substantially improve our extraction speed."/>
	<entry name="Minerals2Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+100% <icon texture='Resources/Minerals'/> minerals"/>
	<entry name="Morale0" value="Holo Theater"/>
	<entry name="Morale0Description" value="After years of hypersleep and inactivity, our people long for distraction and entertainment to stimulate their senses. Holographic 3D projections are the next step towards a virtual reality that promises an exciting experience for the whole family!<br/><br/><style oblique='1'/>&quot;She looks so real!&quot;"/>
	<entry name="Morale0Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+4 <icon texture='Resources/Morale'/> morale"/>
	<entry name="Morale1" value="Emotional Regulation Center"/>
	<entry name="Morale1Description" value="Through neural microsurgery and operant conditioning, all provided by the Emotional Regulation Center, the colonists can subtly alter their dominant alpha waves in case of emotional distress, substantially improving their well-being amidst the harsh environments of Pandora.<br/><br/><style oblique='1'/>&quot;The truth is that we can learn to condition our minds, bodies, and emotions to link pain or pleasure to whatever we choose. By changing what we link pain and pleasure to, we will instantly change our behaviors.&quot;<br/>    -- Anthony Robbins"/>
	<entry name="Morale1Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+8 <icon texture='Resources/Morale'/> morale"/>
	<entry name="Morale2" value="Collective Consciousness"/>
	<entry name="Morale2Description" value="Study of Xenomorph hives has finally allowed the colony to emulate their collective mind through artificial means, while still retaining the human esence of individuals. This allows the colonists to fully realize their empathy, greatly boosting their living environment."/>
	<entry name="Morale2Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+16 <icon texture='Resources/Morale'/> morale"/>
	<entry name="NukeBuilding" value="Missile Launch Control Center"/>
	<entry name="NukeBuildingDescription" value="The main control facility for ballistic missiles silos. From a launch control center, the missile combat crew can monitor the complex, launch the missile, or relax in the living quarters."/>
	<entry name="NukeBuildingProperties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>Launches missile operations"/>
	<entry name="Pollution0" value="Automated Recycling"/>
	<entry name="Pollution0Description" value="Old Earth was in a grim state. With large parts of the ozone layer destroyed as well as the landscape scarred by factional warfare and nuclear waste, our ancestors gathered in a handful of mega cities housing billions of people, trying to escape from an increasingly harsh environment.<br/><br/>Many scientists and ecologists rightfully advocate that such a course of events should not be repeated, and these newly discovered automated recycling technologies are a step in the right direction."/>
	<entry name="Pollution0Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>-4 <icon texture='Resources/Pollution'/> pollution"/>
	<entry name="Pollution1" value="Air Recycler"/>
	<entry name="Pollution1Description" value="The efforts to diminish the impact of industrialization on air purity may have paid and helped the colonists thrive for so long, but the latest breakthroughs allow for the implementation of an Air Recycler that further reduces the effects of pollution in its immediate vicinity."/>
	<entry name="Pollution1Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>-8 <icon texture='Resources/Pollution'/> pollution"/>
	<entry name="Pollution2" value="Atmotron"/>
	<entry name="Pollution2Description" value="Why repair what you can recreate? The Atmotron processes the atmospherical data of a given zone for a while, then reproduces and enhances it by various means ranging from electrolysis to ionization, efficiently suppressing most pollution problems in the area."/>
	<entry name="Pollution2Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>-16 <icon texture='Resources/Pollution'/> pollution"/>
	<entry name="Population0" value="Modular Housing"/>
	<entry name="Population0Description" value="Rather than build housing in an inefficient, inclination-driven way, better space occupation can be achieved by building adaptive, highly reconfigurable accomodations. Those allow us to shelter more colonists in a given area rather than expand indefinitely and erratically."/>
	<entry name="Population0Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+16 <icon texture='Resources/Population'/> population limit"/>
	<entry name="Population1" value="Sky Domes"/>
	<entry name="Population1Description" value="The antigravitation fields produced by high velocity rotation of superconductors allows us to construct floating housing structures, thereby removing most of the space occupation problems of the colony and pushing the population limits even further."/>
	<entry name="Population1Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+32 <icon texture='Resources/Population'/> population limit"/>
	<entry name="Population2" value="Neuromatrix"/>
	<entry name="Population2Description" value="Once a colonist becomes too old to be of any direct use to the colony, his experience and personality can be extracted and burned onto a chip. Those are then linked to a global network which feeds their data to the various digital structures of the colony, allowing the retired to keep participating in its development. This spares their relatives the grief of their loss, while the bodies may be discarded, leaving room for younger, healthier colonists."/>
	<entry name="Population2Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+64 <icon texture='Resources/Population'/> population limit"/>
	<entry name="Production0" value="Reactor Array"/>
	<entry name="Production0Description" value="Claims to this new world are made on the backbone of a working industry, providing goods and services to colonists. However, modern factories are machine-driven and highly automated, providing a considerable production output with little to no human interaction."/>
	<entry name="Production0Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+4 <icon texture='Resources/Production'/> production"/>
	<entry name="Production1" value="Intelligent Factory"/>
	<entry name="Production1Description" value="Among the many uses to which AI can be put, one of the most interesting is the optimization of resource deployment. The Intelligent Factory was to be a proof-of-concept demonstrating the ameliorated organization due to the use of machines. Its efficiency was such that it was almost immediately deployed to a large scale, with no further ado."/>
	<entry name="Production1Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+50% <icon texture='Resources/Production'/> production"/>
	<entry name="Production2" value="Nano Factory"/>
	<entry name="Production2Description" value="Automated production can lead to a great deal of wasted time. Machines become obsolete at a consistent pace, outages can stop a whole production array, and what little human interaction is left only hampers productivity. Self-replication is an efficient and cost-effective answer to those problems."/>
	<entry name="Production2Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+100% <icon texture='Resources/Production'/> production"/>
	<entry name="Research0" value="Quantum Physics Laboratory"/>
	<entry name="Research0Description" value="The classical fields or research can be considered as operators in quantic equations rather than means and ends. This allows for a more thorough understanding of the world around us."/>
	<entry name="Research0Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+4 <icon texture='Resources/Research'/> research"/>
	<entry name="Research1" value="Chaos Laboratory"/>
	<entry name="Research1Description" value="Computational power allows for the diminishing of deterministic chaos. Where once computers rounded numbers, leading to wide fluctuation in predicted results, background recalculation of phase space data in real time has led to results more accurate than one had ever dreamt of, in turn helping other fields develop in a much more efficient manner."/>
	<entry name="Research1Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+50% <icon texture='Resources/Research'/> research"/>
	<entry name="Research2" value="Causality Laboratory"/>
	<entry name="Research2Description" value="Rather than recalculate odds, it was found that better results could be achieved by manipulating cause and consequence, putting branes to an effective use, in turn resulting in better chances of provoking the intended effects and reactions instead of dealing with external and uncontrollable factors."/>
	<entry name="Research2Properties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>+100% <icon texture='Resources/Research'/> research"/>
	<entry name="ScanBuilding" value="Recon Satellite Uplink"/>
	<entry name="ScanBuildingDescription" value="Even though disturbances are quite common in the ionosphere of Pandora, and don't allow us a constant link to reconnaissance satellites, we can still communicate with them quite often and upload orders at a rather consistent pace."/>
	<entry name="ScanBuildingProperties" value="<icon texture='GUI/Bullet'/>Provides a Satellite Scan operation every 5 turns"/>
</language>
